            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> If the numpy project thinks they are harmless, why is Cython generating them ???\n\nNumpy works very hard to make sure they don't break binary compatibility with their classes.  Most other projects don't.\n\nIt's a general warning applied to `cimport`ed extension types rather than to Numpy specifically. So in most non-Numpy cases, if it triggers then it's probably a real problem.\n\nIt doesn't mean it can't be improved but it's worth pointing out that Numpy is an outlier here (albeit the outlier that people most commonly see)",
