        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "But these seem to be warnings about numpy arrays, yes?\n\nDo other extension types generate numpy arrays with other than numpy code?\n\nOr would that be that an extension may have been built with a different version of numpy than its is finding at run time? (which Is what I always assumed was what these were for) But if that's the case, why are they getting triggered when there isn't an actual problem -- these warnings seems to be getting triggered when they are apparently harmless.\n\nAlso, IIUC, `warnings.filterwarnings` is global -- so any code that's using numpy will have these suppressed anyway, unless some other part of the system turns them back on [*].\n\nWhich makes them pretty useless ....\n\nAlso -- I'm confused, but it seems there may be a way to tell Cython not to do this check? In which case, I guess the solution is for library writers to upgrade their code. But I can't find that in the docs right now.\n\n[*] most folks (certainly me) are seeing this in pytest, which, by default, enables all Warnings. It doesn't always show up, because it depends some on import order. Speculating now, if a module that filters the warning is imported after pytest has set itself up, then you won't see it.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n ",
