        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It looks like the C definition that Numpy uses depends on some Numpy macros that make it mostly opaque (at least just a plain Python object)\n\nhttps://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/01bad34ee5d010d296a18a0c15f14db78f898107/numpy/_core/include/numpy/ndarraytypes.h#L825-L830\n\nndetcfd4-python looks to have their own Cython declaration for ndarray rather than using Numpy's and that doesn't have `check_size ignore`\n\nhttps://github.com/Unidata/netcdf4-python/blob/25c1684eae440d733f1ea05ffdeb386b2a9ae559/include/netCDF4.pxi#L376\n\nSo that's what's happening here I think.\n",
